# Update SDK Help Tab When Adding Hooks

When you add a new hook to the SDK (a new file in `src/hooks/use-*.ts` and its export in `src/index.ts`), you **must** also update the developer help documentation in the host application.

## What to Update

**File:** `/Users/dale.hurley/Herd/aiparalegal/resources/js/pages/Admin/SdkApplications/SdkHelpTab.tsx`

### 1. Add a row to the "Available SDK Hooks" table

Find the `<tbody>` inside the `hooks` accordion section and add a new `<tr>` for the hook:

```tsx
<tr>
    <td className="py-2.5 pr-4 font-mono text-xs text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400">useNewHook</td>
    <td className="py-2.5 pr-4">Brief description of what the hook does</td>
    <td className="py-2.5 font-mono text-xs">methodName(args)</td>
</tr>
```

### 2. Optionally add a usage example

If the hook introduces a new capability pattern, add an example code block below the table similar to the existing `useLLM` example.

## Checklist

- [ ] New row added to the hooks table in `SdkHelpTab.tsx`
- [ ] Hook name, description, and key methods are accurate
- [ ] Build the host app to verify no TypeScript errors
